Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[According to OIE's available data, on top of the new LPAI H7N7 outbreak described above in the Western Cape province, there are currently 3 "continuing" outbreaks of avian influenza affecting commercial ostriches in South Africa:

1. HPAI H5N2, which started 12 Apr 2011, so far 50 outbreaks have been recorded in Western and Eastern Cape provinces.
2. LPAI H7N1, which started 19 Jun 2012, so far 14 outbreaks have been recorded in Western and Eastern Cape provinces.
3. LPAI H5N2, which started 4 Oct 2012, so far 9 outbreaks have been recorded in the Western Cape province.

South Africa's ostrich industry is export-dependent. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1EPe.]
